commit.message:
Reset access tokens to original value in provider spec

The provider spec in question would change the access tokens for
multiple Facebook providers. This global state change would affect
downstream tests which are meant to work with the original token
provided in ENV. This change ensures the specs can be run in any order.
Set JSON backend before each providers spec
Reset XML backend before each test
Move #reset_backend to base formatter class
Update spec_helper.rb require statements

Use bundler to setup specs

Sets the load path for gems in the gemfile and the local gem

Reset JSON formatter backend before each test

The YAML and JSON formatter tests were impacting each other due to
changes in global state. This meant it was possible to see different
test results depending on execution order. By resetting the formatter
for each test, we can ensure default behavior and override as needed.

commit.message:
Fix specs with ruby 3.x

With ruby 3.0 some specs fail because the expectation on arguments now
defaults to kwargs instead of a hash. Use explicit hashes in the
expectations to fix this. This change is backward compatible with
older ruby versions.

defaults to kwargs instead of a hash. Use explicit hashes in the
expectations to fix this. This change is backward compatible with
older ruby versions.
